## Netdiscover — Finding Hidden Devices

Nmap uses ping to find devices. Windows blocks ping.
Netdiscover uses ARP — every device must respond to ARP. Even Windows behind a firewall.

```bash
sudo apt install netdiscover
sudo netdiscover -i enp0s3 -r 192.168.1.0/24
```

| Flag | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `-i enp0s3` | Use this network interface |
| `-r 192.168.1.0/24` | Scan this network range |

Press CTRL+C to stop.

