## MAC Address Lookup

Every device has a MAC address. The first half identifies the manufacturer.

Example:
```
e0:ba:ad:40:c2:48 → Hikvision (CCTV camera)
48:4d:7e:b4:db:06 → Dell Inc. (PC)
```

Use this website to look up any MAC address:
```
https://maclookup.app
```

---

## NBTScan — Find Windows Computer Names

```bash
sudo apt install nbtscan
sudo nbtscan 192.168.1.x
```

Output example:
```
192.168.1.202    DESKTOP-N63QS3B    WORKGROUP
```

The computer name helps identify who owns the device.

