## Quick Reference — All Commands

| Command | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `nmap 127.0.0.1` | Scan yourself |
| `nmap -sV <IP>` | Version detection |
| `sudo nmap -O <IP>` | OS detection |
| `sudo nmap -A <IP>` | Full aggressive scan |
| `nmap -Pn <IP>` | Scan hidden devices |
| `nmap 192.168.1.0/24` | Scan entire network |
| `nmap -Pn --open -T4 192.168.1.0/24` | Fast network scan |
| `sudo netdiscover -i enp0s3 -r 192.168.1.0/24` | ARP scan — find all devices |
| `sudo nbtscan <IP>` | Find Windows computer name |
| `nmap -Pn --script smb-os-discovery <IP>` | Get Windows details via SMB |
| `ip a` | Find your own IP address |
